==Learning the ways of the Barbarian==
===Barbarian Firemaking===

==== Part one: Lighting a fire with a bow ====
'''Requirements: {{SCP|Firemaking|35|link=yes}}, {{SCP|Crafting|11|link=yes}}'''

'''''Items required: Any [[bow]] except [[Twisted bow|twisted]], [[Cursed goblin bow|cursed]], [[Dark bow|dark]], [[Crystal bow|crystal]], [[ogre bow|ogre]], [[Rain bow|rain,]] [[Starter bow|starter]]  or the [[signed oak bow]]; oak logs'''''

First, speak to [[Otto]], and ask about the barbarian [[Firemaking]] skills. He will tell you to take a [[bow]] and use it with oaken ([[oak logs|oak]]) logs as a way of lighting them without a [[tinderbox]]. You can use any type of bow ''except'' [[twisted bow]]s, [[cursed goblin bow]]s, [[ogre bow]]s, [[Rain bow|rain bows]], [[Dark bow|dark bows]], [[crystal bow]]s, and the [[signed oak bow]]. Although lighting logs with a bow is fancier, it gives the same experience as lighting them with a tinderbox. Use your logs on the bow to make it less click intensive. After lighting your first logs, speak to Otto again to be able to continue.

