====Part two: [[Pyre ship]]s====
'''Requirements: {{SCP|Firemaking|35|link=yes}}, {{SCP|Crafting|11|link=yes}}'''

'''''Items required: any woodcutting axe, [[tinderbox]] or any [[bow]] except [[Twisted bow|twisted]], [[Cursed goblin bow|cursed]], [[Dark bow|dark]], [[Crystal bow|crystal]], [[ogre bow|ogre]], [[Rain bow|rain]], [[Starter bow|starter]] or the [[signed oak bow]]'''''

''Optional but highly recommended: one-click teleport, food and armour to kill '''level 304 [[mithril dragons]]'''''[[File:Pyre Ship chewed bones.gif|frame|An Ancient Barbarian Spirit being laid to rest]]
Talk to [[Otto]] after you created an oak [[Barbarian skills|bow fire]]. Otto will now explain the art of making a [[pyre ship]] after saying the following.

#Tell him that your mind is ready for [[Firemaking]] wisdom.
#Seek more answers, and ask him, ''"What follows this?"''
'''Warning! The [[Ancient Cavern]] is quite a dangerous area, as it is filled with dragons with long-range attacks, and high-level monsters that can attack using more than one combat style. Additionally, there is no exit immediately available upon entering the dungeon. It would be wise to bring a one-click teleport in case of emergency.'''

You need to enter the [[Ancient Cavern|dungeon]] below the lake and fight the monsters within to obtain [[chewed bones]] or [[mangled bones]] to be used in constructing a pyre ship. You will need some sort of [[woodcutting axe]] to carve the pyre ship and a [[tinderbox]] or a suitable bow to ignite it.

High-level [[dragons]] will use a [[magic]]-based attack on you immediately after descending the steps in the dungeon. Don't bring in anything you are not willing to lose.

When rummaging through barbarian skeletons found on the ground or when killing the various barbarians within the cavern, you may find mangled bones. The only way to get chewed bones, however, is to kill [[mithril dragons]]. Both chewed and mangled bones, in conjunction with any type of log, can be used on the burnt spaces (pyre sites), found scattered around the lake near [[Otto's house]], to make a pyre ship. Burning a pyre ship will grant the player an experience bonus of up to 300%, depending on the logs used, the next time they bury [[bones]].

Spirits released from chewed bones are benevolent and will give you [[Chewed bones#Rewards|some items]], including a slim chance for a [[dragon full helm]], while spirits released from mangled bones are [[aggressive]] [[ferocious barbarian spirit]]s. Please note that if you use [[mangled bones]] to make a pyre ship, you will be unable to make another pyre ship until you kill the spirit.
If you attempt to make another one while a barbarian spirit is around, the sacrifice will be declined.

'''Completing the barbarian skills book requires burning [[chewed bones]] dropped by [[mithril dragons]].''' Otherwise, the final paragraph of the section on [[crafting]] pyre ships will be missing, and page 21 of the book will be blank even if the rest of the training has been completed. You will also need to speak to Otto again after burning the bones.

Pyre ships have a [[firemaking]] and [[crafting]] level requirement. Crafting and Firemaking CAN be boosted to make pyre ships.

