===Barbarian Fishing===

[[Otto]] will give the player information about Barbarian [[Fishing]]. 

Requirements for heavy rod fishing: {{SCP|Fishing|48|link=yes}}, {{SCP|Agility|15|link=yes}}, {{SCP|Strength|15|link=yes}} 

Requirements for bare-handed fishing: {{SCP|Fishing|55|link=yes}}, {{SCP|Agility|15|link=yes}}, {{SCP|Strength|35|link=yes}} 

There are two types of activities that fall under Barbarian Fishing: [[Barbarian rod|heavy rod fishing]] and bare-hand fishing. A player looking to complete [[Barbarian Training#Barbarian Smithing|Barbarian Smithing]] must have Otto train them under <u>both</u> types.

You do not need to complete both sections to begin fishing in the nearby waters with a [[Barbarian rod]].

====Part one: Heavy Rod Fishing====
[[File:Average heavy rod fishing XP rates.png|thumb|Barbarian fishing experience rates using a heavy rod as a function of fishing level.]]
Speak to [[Otto]] and then ask about fishing rod methods. He will tell you that barbarians use stronger fishing rods to catch leaping fish in the lake nearby. Search under his bed and collect a heavy [[barbarian rod]]; make sure to also have [[fishing bait]] or [[feathers]] on you. Use the fishing spots around the lake and hook a leaping fish. The [[Cooking]] experience refers to the amount of experience received from successfully gutting the fish with a knife and obtaining [[roe]] or [[caviar]] as well as a good chance of obtaining [[fishing offcuts|fish offcuts]], which can be used as bait for this fishing method. Roe and caviar can also be used as bait if there are no feathers, offcuts, or fishing bait in the player's inventory. At 80 cooking it is no longer possible to fail cutting salmon and sturgeon.

